      • ARGUMENT_BEGIN

        public static char ARGUMENT_BEGIN
        The character that indicates the following information is arguments of a command, up until the matching ARGUMENT_END. The java equivalent of this is '('.

      • ARGUMENT_END

        public static char ARGUMENT_END
        The character that indicates the end of the arguments for a command. This follows a matching ARGUMENT_BEGIN. The java equivalent of this is ')'.

      • STRING_CHAR

        public static char STRING_CHAR
        The character that is used to begin and end strings inside of commands. The java equivalent of this is '''.

      • COMMENT_CHAR

        public static char COMMENT_CHAR
        The character that is used to signify that the following line is a comment and should not be executed. The Java equivalent of this is "//".

      • COMPILER_CHAR

        public static char COMPILER_CHAR
        The character used to specify that the following line should not be executed but is a set of instructions for the compiler. This is similar to the '#' in C++.

      • ARGUMENT_SEPARATOR

        public static char ARGUMENT_SEPARATOR
        The character used to separate different arguments in a method. The Java equivalent of this is ','.
